Date: Tue 17 Apr 2001 18:08
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: El Mercurio [Transl. by Mod.MPP [edited
<http://www.emol.com/noticias/detalle/detalle_noticia.asp?idnoticia=52398>

New case of hantavirus infection confirmed in Puerto Montt
----------------------------------------------------------
PUERTO MONTT - A new case of hantavirus [pulmonary syndrome was confirmed
today in a 52-year-old woman in critical condition at the Internal Medicine
Service of the Puerto Montt Hospital. The woman was admitted to the
hospital on Fri 6 Apr 2001 after being infected in the rural commune of
Chaiten, where she resides. Upon confirmation of the disease, a team from
the rural health service was sent to investigate and instruct the family
and nearby neighbors in sanitary measures that should be adopted [to avoid
further cases.
Related articles on Hantavirus in El Mercurio are the following:
New case of hantavirus in the 10th Region (10 Apr 2001);
